Project Description: 

Grazioso Salvare Dashboard is an interactive web application desifned to filter and display data on Animal Outcomes It contains an interactive filter, an interactive data table, a geolocation chart, and a pie chart. 

 

Tools Used: 

Python: used for scripting and data manipulation. 

Dash: used as a Framework for building web applications. 

MongoDB: our database used for storing and retrieving animal data 

Plotly: used for creating interactive charts and graphs 

 

MongoDB Explanation: 

MongoDB was chosen for its ability to handle large volumes of unstructured data. It was also chosen for its ability to ease of use when interfacing with Python via the Pymongo library. 

 

Dash Framework Explanation: 

Dash was chosen to provide a simple yet powerful framework for building web applications in conjunction with Python. It allows for interactive, real-time data visualization and integrates seamlessly with Plotly when creating charts and maps. 

 

Steps Taken: 

Setup MongoDB and Python Environment. 

Develop CRUD Operations: implemented in Animal_Shelter.py 

Build Dashboard Layout: Created interactive filters, data tables, and charts in ProjectTwoDashboard.ipynb 

Implement callbacks: added interactivity to update charts and data tables based on filters. 

Testing and debugging: ensured that all components worked as intended. 

 

Challenges and solutions: 

Authentication errors: if this occurs then adjust the parameters of the CRUD module to resolve these issues. 



