         Whenever I encounter a problem, I start off with the problem, the solution and the steps taken towards the solution. I do this by breaking down the problem into smaller problems until I have a problem with an obvoius solution.
         I then enact it and continue building upon my success until the total problem is solved. This also allows me to gain wisdom and experience when dealing with similar problems in the future.
